speech.p:
Queen's recommendation having been signified—Motion made and Question proposed, That, for the purposes of any Act of the present Session to make further provision with respect to the British National Oil Corporation, to abolish the National Oil Account, to make further provision with respect to the British Gas Corporation and to make provision for and in connection with the supply of gas through pipes by persons other than the Corporation, it is expedient to authorise the payment out of moneys provided by Parliament of—
(1) any sums required by the Secretary of State for making payments by way of consideration for any shares transferred to him by order under the Act;
(2) any sums required by the Secretary of State for making grants to the British National Oil Corporation or any of its wholly owned subsidiaries towards expenditure incurred by the Corporation or subsidiary in or in connection with the exercise of the power conferred on the Corporation by section 2(1)(e) of the Petroleum and Submarine Pipe-lines Act 1975;
(3) any administrative expenses of the Secretary of State; and
(4) any increase attributable to the provisions of the Act in the sums which under any other enactment are paid out of moneys so provided.
And that it is expedient to authorise the payment of any sums into the National Loans Fund or the Consolidated Fund.—[Mr. Brooke.]
